content: Rachelle is a name of French origin, which is a variant of the name Rachel, meaning "ewe" in Hebrew. People with the name Rachelle are often described as friendly, kind-hearted, and creative individuals who enjoy helping others. They are also known for their intelligence, intuition, and emotional sensitivity. Rachelle is a beautiful and feminine name with a positive connotation, and it may appeal to parents looking for a name that is both classic and distinctive.
